## Release Decision

### Go

Use when:

- All milestone exit criteria are met.
- No blocker or critical defects remain.
- Remaining major defects are explicitly accepted.
- The build represents the intended vertical-slice experience.

### Conditional Go

Use when:

- No blocker or critical defects remain.
- A limited issue has a documented workaround.
- The issue does not compromise the portfolio objective.
- An owner and follow-up date are assigned.

### No-Go

Use when:

- A progression-blocking issue remains.
- A Must-have feature is incomplete.
- The build is unstable or cannot be distributed reliably.
- Testing results do not support the intended player experience.

